article.headline: Iona 59, Loyola, Md. 50
article.story: BALTIMORE -- Rashard McGill scored six of his 12 points in a key second-half run to help Iona defeat Loyola 59-50 on Monday night. Leading 39-37 with 3:18 to go, the Greyhounds (11-6, 3-3 Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference) used strong defensive play to spark a 14-4 run, lasting almost 12 minutes. Iona forced eight turnovers and held Loyola (8-8, 1-5) to just 1 of 10 shooting from the field during the spurt. Rashon Dwight capped the run on two free throws for a 53-41 lead with 3:18 left to play. Kyle Smith scored 12 points, Alejo Rodriguez had 11 and Dwight finished with 10 for the Gaels. Iona forced 22 turnovers and held the Greyhounds to 38.1 percent shooting (16 of 42). Brian Rudolph and Anthony Winbush scored 13 points each for Loyola, which outrebounded Iona 39-31. The Greyhounds' Julius Brooks tallied a career-high four blocks.
